Usage: focus [-o|--output OUTPUT-FILE] [--no-color] [-f|--full] [-i|--in-place] 
             [-s|--silent] [-a|--align] SCRIPT [FILES...]

  Focus - cli utility for hacking and slashing data

Available options:
  -o,--output OUTPUT-FILE  File to use for output. Defaults to stdout if
                           unspecified
  --no-color               Disable colored output
  -f,--full                Process the entire input at once instead of
                           line-by-line
  -i,--in-place            Modify each input file in place rather than writing
                           to output
  -s,--silent              Suppress warnings
  -a,--align               Align the input files line by line. Refer to them
                           using %f1, %f2, etc.
  SCRIPT                   Focus script to run
  FILES...                 Input files. If omitted, read from stdin
  -h,--help                Show this help text
